  • Methodendetails

    • get

      public static PlantType get(String name)
      Getting a custom PlantType, or an existing one if it has the same name as that one. Your plant should implement IPlantable and return this custom type in IPlantable.getPlantType(BlockGetter, BlockPos).

      If your new plant grows on blocks like any one of them above, never create a new PlantType. This Type is only functioning in Block.canSustainPlant(BlockState, BlockGetter, BlockPos, Direction, IPlantable), which you are supposed to override this function in your new block and create a new plant type to grow on that block. This method can be called during parallel loading

      Parameter:
      name - the name of the type of plant, you had better follow the style above
      Gibt zurück:
      the acquired PlantType, a new one if not found.
